title: BBC Army Behind the New Frontlines Series 1 3of3 Keeping the Pea
description: Army Behind the New Frontlines: Series 1 War Documentary hosted by David Harewood, published by BBC in 2017 - English narration http://docuwiki.net/images/2/26/Army-Behind-the-New-Frontlines-Series-1-Cover.jpg Information ------------------------------ Army: Behind the New Frontlines Filmed over 18 months, this series goes into the heart of the British Army. Through the eyes of the rank and file and the leaders, it shows the challenges of fighting wars when we are not at war. 3) Keeping the Peace in South Sudan In this episode, the British Army is deployed on a UN peacekeeping operation to protect thousands escaping South Sudan's civil war. In a country where government troops can be lawless and corrupt, can the British Army help build peace and stop genocide? South Sudan is the world's newest country. It gained independence from Sudan in 2011 but quickly descended into civil war.
